Sentencas: This paper sets out the results of mathematical modeling and numerical simulations with regard to the influences of the type and thickness of electrolyte on Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Hybrid System (SOFC-HS) performance.
Titulo: Influences of the type and thickness of electrolyte on solid oxide fuel cell hybrid system performance

Sentencas: A change of electrolyte materials can result in total hybrid system efficiency increasing from around 48% HHV (53% LHV) to about 65% HHV (72 % LHV) in an environment where turbine inlet temperature and gas turbine subsystem pressure ratio remain unchanged.
Titulo: Influences of the type and thickness of electrolyte on solid oxide fuel cell hybrid system performance

Sentencas: The governing equations of SOFGHS modeling are given.
Titulo: Influences of the type and thickness of electrolyte on solid oxide fuel cell hybrid system performance

Sentencas: An adequate simulator of the SOFC stack was made and described.
Titulo: Influences of the type and thickness of electrolyte on solid oxide fuel cell hybrid system performance

Sentencas: Based on this simulator a model of the 260 kWe Siemens Westing house unit was built.
Titulo: Influences of the type and thickness of electrolyte on solid oxide fuel cell hybrid system performance

Sentencas: The performance of this SOFC-HS with different electrolyte materials and thicknesses is shown, and some characteristics are given and described.
Titulo: Influences of the type and thickness of electrolyte on solid oxide fuel cell hybrid system performance

Sentencas: The advantages and disadvantages of different electrolyte types from a hybrid system performance point of view are indicated.
Titulo: Influences of the type and thickness of electrolyte on solid oxide fuel cell hybrid system performance
